					<div id="mw-content-text" class="mw-body-content"><div class="mw-content-ltr mw-parser-output" lang="en" dir="ltr"><div class="shortdescription nomobile noexcerpt noprint searchaux" style="display:none">Buddhist festival marking the birth, enlightenment and death of the Buddha</div>
<div role="note" class="hatnote navigation-not-searchable">This article is about a Buddhist festival. For the unrelated Hindu and Sikh new year festival, see <a href="/wiki/Vaisakhi" title="Vaisakhi">Vaisakhi</a>. For the Buddha's disciple, see <a href="/wiki/Visakha" title="Visakha">Visakha</a>.</div>
<p class="mw-empty-elt"> 
 
</p>
<table class="infobox vevent"><tbody><tr><th colspan="2" class="infobox-above hd" style="background-color: palegoldenrod">Vesak</th></tr><tr><td colspan="2" class="infobox-image"><span class="mw-default-size" typeof="mw:File/Frameless"><a href="/wiki/File:Vesak_Day_2555.jpg" class="mw-file-description"><img src="//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/5/50/Vesak_Day_2555.jpg/240px-Vesak_Day_2555.jpg" decoding="async" width="240" height="194" class="mw-file-element" srcset="//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/5/50/Vesak_Day_2555.jpg/360px-Vesak_Day_2555.jpg 1.5x, //upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/5/50/Vesak_Day_2555.jpg/480px-Vesak_Day_2555.jpg 2x" data-file-width="2018" data-file-height="1630" /></a></span><div class="infobox-caption" style="caption">Vesak Day celebrations at <a href="/wiki/Borobodur" class="mw-redirect" title="Borobodur">Borobodur</a> in <a href="/wiki/Central_Java" title="Central Java">Central Java</a>, <a href="/wiki/Indonesia" title="Indonesia">Indonesia</a></div></td></tr><tr><th scope="row" class="infobox-label">Official name</th><td class="infobox-data">Vesak, Vesākha, Buddha Jayanti, Buddha Purnima, Vaishakh Purnima, Saka Dawa</td></tr><tr><th scope="row" class="infobox-label">Also called</th><td class="infobox-data"><a href="/wiki/Buddha%27s_Birthday" title="Buddha&#39;s Birthday">Buddha's Birthday</a> or Buddha Day</td></tr><tr><th scope="row" class="infobox-label">Type</th><td class="infobox-data">Buddhist</td></tr><tr><th scope="row" class="infobox-label">Significance</th><td class="infobox-data summary">Commemoration of the birth, enlightenment and death of the <a href="/wiki/The_Buddha" title="The Buddha">The Buddha</a></td></tr><tr><th scope="row" class="infobox-label">Observances</th><td class="infobox-data"><a href="/wiki/Buddhist_meditation" title="Buddhist meditation">Meditation</a>, observing the <a href="/wiki/Eight_Precepts" class="mw-redirect" title="Eight Precepts">Eight Precepts</a>, partaking of vegetarian food, giving to charity, "bathing" the Buddha</td></tr><tr><th scope="row" class="infobox-label">Date</th><td class="infobox-data">Full moon of the lunar month of Vesākha, usually in April, May or June.</td></tr><tr><th scope="row" class="infobox-label">2023&#160;date</th><td class="infobox-data"><div class="plainlist">
<ul><li>3 May (Myanmar)<sup id="cite_ref-1" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-1">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup></li>
<li>4 May (Malaysia)<sup id="cite_ref-PublicHolidaysMY_2-0" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-PublicHolidaysMY-2">&#91;2&#93;</a></sup></li>
